WEBVTT

00:06.206 --> 00:09.543 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening. I'm
Judy Woodruff. Gwen Ifill is
away.

00:09.543 --> 00:13.947 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:
President Obama delivers his
final State of the Union
address.

00:13.947 --> 00:17.918 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
His chief of staff talks to
us about what to expect.

00:17.918 --> 00:24.625 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Then: A suicide bomber in Turkey
kills 10 foreigners in a popular
tourist spot.

00:24.625 --> 00:29.596 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, finally, a successful
program helping underserved
students prepare for and get
into

00:29.596 --> 00:31.331 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
college.

00:31.331 --> 00:35.836 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ANDREA RUIZ DIAZ, Student: When
you're an immigrant and you're
in America, you're just

00:35.836 --> 00:38.772 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
focusing on learning the
language, graduating from high
school. You're not really
focusing

00:38.772 --> 00:40.607 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
