00:40.607 --> 00:43.176 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's "PBS NewsHour."

00:43.176 --> 00:48.348 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:48.348 --> 01:03.130 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Iran picked up 10
U.S. Navy sailors and their two
small boats in the Persian

01:03.130 --> 01:09.303 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Gulf today. U.S. officials
reported one boat had mechanical
trouble and ran aground. Iran

01:09.303 --> 01:14.341 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
said the crews were detained for
trespassing. It happened near
Farsi Island. The Pentagon

01:14.341 --> 01:19.446 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
said the vessels were moving
between Kuwait and Bahrain at
the time.

01:19.446 --> 01:24.117 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Afterward, officials said Iran's
foreign minister assured
Secretary of State John Kerry
that

01:24.117 --> 01:28.555 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the sailors and their boats
will be handed over promptly.

01:28.555 --> 01:33.360 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Persian Gulf incident came
as President Obama was putting
the finishing touches on

01:33.360 --> 01:38.699 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
his last State of the Union
address. He's expected to use
the prime-time speech to talk

01:38.699 --> 01:44.805 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
about where he sees the country
headed for years to come,
including after he leaves
office.

01:44.805 --> 01:49.743 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But House Speaker Paul Ryan and
other Republicans talked up
their own ideas today on what
the

01:49.743 --> 01:53.647 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
president should say, especially
when it comes to fighting
terrorism.

01:53.647 --> 01:57.484 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
REP. PAUL RYAN (R-WI), Speaker
of the House: While we're not
certainly expecting much new,

01:57.484 --> 02:02.456 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
there is one thing that we hope
to hear from the president, and
that is a comprehensive

02:02.456 --> 02:07.527 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
plan to defeat ISIS. Americans
are so anxious right now about
their security, about what's

02:07.527 --> 02:10.130 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
going on around the world.

02:10.130 --> 02:14.501 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: On the Democratic
side, Washington Senator Patty
Murray acknowledged there's

02:14.501 --> 02:18.672 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
more work to be done and urged
both parties to pitch in.

02:18.672 --> 02:21.641 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
SEN. PATTY MURRAY (D),
Washington: Tonight's speech is
going to be about the future of

02:21.641 --> 02:27.180 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
our great country. And Democrats
are ready to keep working here
in Congress to make sure

02:27.180 --> 02:31.084 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that future works for families
and the middle class.

02:31.084 --> 02:33.520 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We will get a
preview of tonight's address,
and talk to the president's
chief

02:33.520 --> 02:37.391 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
of staff, after
the news summary.

02:37.391 --> 02:42.729 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In the presidential race, Vice
President Joe Biden weighed in
Monday on the Democratic

02:42.729 --> 02:48.235 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
contest and offered words of
praise for Bernie Sanders. New
polls have the Vermont senator

02:48.235 --> 02:54.641 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
leading Hillary Clinton in New
Hampshire and moving up closer
to her in Iowa. In a CNN

02:54.641 --> 02:58.178 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
interview, the vice president
said Sanders has more
credibility on the issue of
income

02:58.178 --> 02:59.813 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
inequality.

02:59.813 --> 03:04.351 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOSEPH BIDEN, Vice President of
the United States: Bernie is
speaking to a yearning that

03:04.351 --> 03:07.721 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
is deep and real.

03:07.721 --> 03:13.393 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It is relatively new for Hillary
to talk about that. Hillary's
focus has been other things

03:13.393 --> 03:18.131 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
