unconstitutional. Judges in the
state have the final say in

05:47.747 --> 05:53.853 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
capital cases and can even
impose a death sentence when a
jury decides against it. Today's

05:53.853 --> 06:01.094 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
decision could mean new appeals
for some of the 390 people on
Florida's death row.

06:01.094 --> 06:07.634 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On Wall Street, stocks gained
ground, even as oil prices fell
to near $30 a barrel, and

06:07.634 --> 06:13.974 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
pulled energy shares lower.
Despite that, the Dow Jones
industrial average gained 117

06:13.974 --> 06:23.550 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
points to close at 16516. The
Nasdaq rose nearly 48 points,
and the S&amp;P 500 added 15.

06:23.550 --> 06:29.456 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the University of Alabama
celebrated its fourth college
football national championship

06:29.456 --> 06:37.230 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
since 2009 today. The Crimson
Tide beat Clemson last night
45-40. And per tradition, coach

06:37.230 --> 06:44.004 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Nick Saban got a Gatorade shower
from his players. Bet it
probably felt good.

06:44.004 --> 06:48.608 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
