07:25.745 --> 07:32.485 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: President Obama
wasted no time kicking off his
2016, just five days

07:32.485 --> 07:35.889 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
into the new year, with a highly
publicized announcement that
he's going it alone on certain

07:35.889 --> 07:38.158 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
gun control measures.

07:38.158 --> 07:42.128 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, President of the
United States: There are actions
within my legal authority

07:42.128 --> 07:46.132 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that we can take to help reduce
gun violence and save more
lives, actions that protect

07:46.132 --> 07:49.369 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
our rights and our kids.

07:49.369 --> 07:55.108 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: The president
is well aware his days in office
are numbered, 374, to be

07:55.108 --> 07:59.612 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
exact. And so are the items he
can tackle in that time. What
kind of meaningful action

07:59.612 --> 08:03.917 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
could the outgoing leader get
done? That depends who you ask.

08:03.917 --> 08:06.553 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JOHN FEEHERY, Republican
Strategist: You look at the
president's biggest
accomplishments,

08:06.553 --> 08:10.457 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they all happened in the first
two years of his presidency. And
he's been trying to protect

08:10.457 --> 08:12.926 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
