Bush, President Obama faces a
Congress run by strong
opposition.

09:39.913 --> 09:43.283 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MAN: This is a 15-minute vote.

09:43.283 --> 09:49.489 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: The
Republican-led House started its
2016 by passing a repeal of
Obama's

09:49.489 --> 09:53.893 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
signature Affordable Care Act,
sending it to Obama's desk to
force a veto.

09:53.893 --> 09:56.663 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REP. PAUL RYAN (R-WI), Speaker
of the House: This is the
closest that we have come to
repealing

09:56.663 --> 10:00.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
