He's not sure about the
president himself. He says the
president

14:12.852 --> 14:16.055 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
has to be genuine and really
speak to what he means.

14:16.055 --> 14:18.424 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Ah, the
wisdom of real people.

14:18.424 --> 14:20.126 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: That's right.

14:20.126 --> 14:22.895 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Just very
quickly, Lisa, you have been
covering Congress for a while.
Does

14:22.895 --> 14:26.299 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
it feel different that this is
the last State of the Union?

14:26.299 --> 14:29.569 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: I'm going to be
honest, Judy. It doesn't feel
all that different.

14:29.569 --> 14:33.339 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
To me, this feels a little bit
like a classic State of the
Union. I

14:33.339 --> 14:37.376 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
think there's been a bigger
change that could be expressed
in this speech tonight. I think

14:37.376 --> 14:42.181 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
what is different in Congress at
this moment that I feel is that
now it is about competing

14:42.181 --> 14:46.619 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
agendas. It's not as much about
the competing politics that we
have seen.

14:46.619 --> 14:50.523 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And I think that's being
expressed tonight, as the
president tries to express a
bigger

14:50.523 --> 14:54.694 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
vision that they say is beyond
politics. Republicans are trying
to do the same. But what's
ironic

14:54.694 --> 14:58.197 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
there is, of course, that's
kind of politics, too.

14:58.197 --> 15:01.134 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Lisa Desjardins,
reporting for us from the
Capitol, and we will be talking

15:01.134 --> 15:02.435 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to you later tonight. Thanks.

15:02.435 --> 15:05.538 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: You got it.

15:05.538 --> 15:09.075 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Reports have it
that President Obama, White
House speechwriters and his
staff

15:09.075 --> 15:12.678 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
have spent today tweaking the
State of the Union address.

15:12.678 --> 15:16.983 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A short time ago, I spoke with
the White House chief of staff,
Denis McDonough.

15:16.983 --> 15:19.318 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Denis McDonough, welcome.

15:19.318 --> 15:21.988 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, we're hearing this is going
to be a different sort of State
of the Union. What does that

15:21.988 --> 15:23.623 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
mean?

15:23.623 --> 15:26.659 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DENIS MCDONOUGH, White House
Chief of Staff: Judy, thanks for
the chance to be with you.

15:26.659 --> 15:31.664 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Well, the president -- you won't
hear tonight what is a
traditional list of policy
proposals,

15:31.664 --> 15:35.735 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
but, rather, you will hear the
president talk through the kind
of challenges that we will

15:35.735 --> 15:38.771 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
be facing not only in the year
ahead, but really the decade
ahead.

15:38.771 --> 15:43.442 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he wants to make sure that
the institutions of Washington
are focused on those, and are

15:43.442 --> 15:47.713 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
rolling up our sleeves to get
ready to deal with a changing
economy where everybody needs

15:47.713 --> 15:53.619 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to have a shot at opportunity in
this economy, talking about
using all the elements of our

15:53.619 --> 15:58.658 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
national power to protect the
country and expand our
influence, making sure that we

15:58.658 --> 16:03.663 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
use technology to advance our
interests, not use that -- not
have that technology used

16:03.663 --> 16:08.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
against us, and then, of course,
talking about how he thinks our
politics could be done much

16:08.267 --> 16:10.336 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
better than they have been.

16:10.336 --> 16:14.574 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he will make sure that our
politics reflect the greatness
of this country.

16:14.574 --> 16:19.178 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, not putting
forward a list of proposals,
some are interpreting that to

16:19.178 --> 16:23.349 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
mean he doesn't think he can get
much done this year, especially
with Congress.

16:23.349 --> 16:28.054 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DENIS MCDONOUGH: Yes, well,
look, a lot of people said that
to us a year ago. And over

16:28.054 --> 16:31.591 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the course of the last year, we
got a deal with Cuba to open up
and establish diplomatic

16:31.591 --> 16:33.559 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
relations.

16:33.559 --> 16:40.299 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We got a budget deal, a tax
deal. We got TPA, which is a
trade negotiating authority. And

16:40.299 --> 16:47.039 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
then we were able to get the
largest trade agreement in the
history of trade agreements

16:47.039 --> 16:50.509 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
last year. And then, of course,
we got the climate deal in Paris
at the end of the year,

16:50.509 --> 16:55.581 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on top of the budget and on top
of all sorts of reforms and
export financing and other

16:55.581 --> 16:57.450 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
things.

16:57.450 --> 17:03.456 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, we will let the record speak
for itself. This president has
been, obviously, leading

17:03.456 --> 17:11.397 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
policy debates for some time and
pushing the quickest recovery in
terms of job growth over

17:11.397 --> 17:16.402 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the last two years since back in
the 1990s and the quickest
reduction in the unemployment

17:16.402 --> 17:19.906 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
rate since well over
three decades ago.

17:19.906 --> 17:22.275 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, not only do we have ideas.
We're implementing them. You
will hear more about that over
the

17:22.275 --> 17:24.677 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
course of the year.

17:24.677 --> 17:27.446 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, tonight, you will hear
about our challenges, how we're
going to confront them, how
we're

17:27.446 --> 17:30.383 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
going to draw on the strength of
all the American people to
confront them.

17:30.383 --> 17:35.421 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: You mentioned
politics. The Republican
candidates are out there
painting

17:35.421 --> 17:38.925 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a pretty negative picture of the
State of the Union. It sounds
like you're saying the

17:38.925 --> 17:41.193 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
president wants to counter that.

17:41.193 --> 17:44.697 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DENIS MCDONOUGH: Well, I think
the president wants to be
factual.

17:44.697 --> 17:49.669 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think what he sees is an
American people who are -- when
they're working together and

17:49.669 --> 17:55.608 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
focused on the opportunities,
the sky's the limit for this
country. And I do find myself

17:55.608 --> 18:00.413 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
-- and I think the speech
tonight will lay this out a
little bit -- puzzled, perplexed

18:00.413 --> 18:05.351 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
by the fact that these guys --
guys primarily -- want to just
talk down the economy, talk

18:05.351 --> 18:08.321 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
down the United States.

18:08.321 --> 18:12.291 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's not consistent with
either the situation we find
ourselves in today or the
history

18:12.291 --> 18:15.394 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of this great country. So we
will continue to press that
case, and you will hear it
tonight.

18:15.394 --> 18:19.198 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, given the
fact, Denis McDonough, that
two-thirds of the American

18:19.198 --> 18:23.402 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
people, give or take, are
telling pollsters they think the
country is off on the wrong

18:23.402 --> 18:26.672 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
track, what is the president
going to say to change their
mind? What is he going to

18:26.672 --> 18:29.308 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
say the state of the union is?

18:29.308 --> 18:34.313 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DENIS MCDONOUGH: Look, I think
there's no doubt that people
coming -- what we came out

18:34.313 --> 18:39.885 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of, that great recession, the
deepest rescission since the
Great Depression that started in

18:39.885 --> 18:44.991 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
2007-2008, where people saw the
values of their homes wiped out,
people saw their retirements,

18:44.991 --> 18:49.762 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
all the indicators of stability
for their families really took a
dramatic hit.

18:49.762 --> 18:56.502 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, I don't doubt that people
feel uneasy, and they have every
right to feel uneasy.

18:56.502 --> 19:01.340 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Our role, as the leaders in this
country, is to make sure that
we're making opportunities

19:01.340 --> 19:07.346 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for all the American people,
that they have the training, the
opportunities for growth,

19:07.346 --> 19:09.582 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the new jobs that we have been
talking about. And that's what
we are going to talk about

19:09.582 --> 19:11.283 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
tonight.

19:11.283 --> 19:14.820 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Is there worry at
the White House, finally, Denis
McDonough, that what

19:14.820 --> 19:18.924 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the president wants to do this
year could get completely
overwhelmed by, frankly, the

19:18.924 --> 19:22.228 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
2016 presidential race?

19:22.228 --> 19:27.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DENIS MCDONOUGH: We don't spend
a lot of time worrying about the
politics or the races.

19:27.633 --> 19:31.904 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What we spend a lot of time
worrying about is that this
country is ready for this
changing

19:31.904 --> 19:37.510 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and dynamic economy, so people
have opportunities, that we are
focused on the threats to this

19:37.510 --> 19:41.914 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
country, that we're focused on
the new opportunities,
particularly the clean energy.

19:41.914 --> 19:46.018 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, that's what we will focus
on. What happens on the campaign
trail is not something we

19:46.018 --> 19:50.489 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
can control, and we're not even
going to try. We have a story to
tell. We have a country

19:50.489 --> 19:54.060 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to lead, and this is a great
country. And we're blessed to
have the opportunity to do

19:54.060 --> 19:56.495 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
it. That's what we're going
to do for the next year.

19:56.495 --> 19:59.732 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Denis McDonough,
White House chief of staff,
thank you very much for talking

19:59.732 --> 20:03.402 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
with us.

20:03.402 --> 20:11.410 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
DENIS MCDONOUGH:
Thank you, Judy.

20:11.410 --> 20:16.949 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Stay with us.

20:16.949 --> 20:24.023 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour":
relief for starving families in
Syria, but how long will it
last?;

20:24.023 --> 20:31.597 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
