poetry.

20:31.597 --> 20:37.636 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, first, the deadly bombing
that shook Turkey's largest city
today. The suicide blast

20:37.636 --> 20:42.942 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
killed 10 people, including
eight Germans, and wounded 15.

20:42.942 --> 20:46.779 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Chief foreign affairs
correspondent Margaret Warner
has the story.

20:46.779 --> 20:52.318 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MARGARET WARNER: It was
mid-morning when the explosion
ripped through the historic
heart

20:52.318 --> 20:57.923 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
of Istanbul. The site,
Sultanahmet Square, is a major
tourist destination, home to a

20:57.923 --> 21:02.661 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
landmark obelisk and just steps
from the famed Blue Mosque.

21:02.661 --> 21:07.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, today, its grounds were
scattered with bodies, and body
parts, as ambulance sirens

21:07.700 --> 21:12.538 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
wailed and security forces
rushed to the scene.

21:12.538 --> 21:15.074 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN (through translator): It was
a suicide bomb. There was chaos.
Everybody was running

21:15.074 --> 21:16.742 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
somewhere.

21:16.742 --> 21:21.313 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: The dead were
all foreigners, nearly all of
them, German tourists.

21:21.313 --> 21:25.518 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And Reuters correspondent Ayla
Jean Yackley in Istanbul said
via Skype it's a blow to

21:25.518 --> 21:28.721 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Turkey's vital tourist industry.

21:28.721 --> 21:35.594 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AYLA JEAN YACKLEY, Reuters:
There is very much a sense of
deep sadness, fear. What does

21:35.594 --> 21:40.399 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
this mean for Turkey's tourism
business? What does this mean
for Turkey's reputation or

21:40.399 --> 21:45.871 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
standing in the world? Will
Turkey now be perceived as
another dangerous no-go place

21:45.871 --> 21:50.476 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the region? These are some of
the questions that are on
people's minds here as well.

21:50.476 --> 21:53.045 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MARGARET WARNER: Turkish
officials responded quickly,
with the prime minister
declaring

21:53.045 --> 21:56.882 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the Islamic State group
was responsible.

21:56.882 --> 22:01.720 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AHMET DAVUTOGLU, Turkish Prime
Minister (through translator):
Our fight against ISIS, which

22:01.720 --> 22:06.325 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
carried out this attack, will
continue with determination. The
perpetrators of this attack

22:06.325 --> 22:10.362 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and their links will be unveiled
and they will get the punishment
they deserve.

22:10.362 --> 22:14.934 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: Turkey's deputy
prime minister said the
perpetrator was a Syrian
national

22:14.934 --> 22:19.405 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
born in 1988, that he'd entered
Turkey recently, but wasn't on
the country's watch list of

22:19.405 --> 22:22.975 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
suspected militants.

22:22.975 --> 22:28.214 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
